<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="1313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1313">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/725.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Report results representations for modification mining decree March 1.
                            Many American citizens assert operation this decree would necessarily
                            result in confiscation their property and Department desires you take
                            strong action on this ground.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>